Between 1987 and 1993, hunger was endemic in much of the Third World,
which had a growing debt.  Although some blamed Third World
governments, developed nations were asked to forgive debts--some banks
canceled loans--and increase financial aid.  The World Bank began
programs to ease poverty and micro-enterprise lending was
succeeding.</SUM>
